    "updated_at": "2013-11-29T11:31:35Z",
    "body": "In theory `~fn` doesn't exist anymore:\n\n``` rust\nfn main() {\n    let _: ~fn();\n}\n```\n\n```\ntwiddle-fn.rs:2:11: 2:12 error: obsolete syntax: managed or owned closure\ntwiddle-fn.rs:2     let _: ~fn();\n                           ^\nnote: managed closures have been removed and owned closures are now written `proc()`\n```\n\nso (some part of) it is certainly a bug rather than by design. (I guess the bug could just be the error message... _shrugs_)\n",
