    "updated_at": "2013-11-29T15:27:12Z",
    "body": "When rustc reads `let f = proc() {};`, `f` is inferred as `~fn()` rather than `proc()` (== `~once fn()`). I've seen the behavior when `~fn()` was not obsolete yet.\n",
